s of dough at a time and cover remaining dough with a damp kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","For best results, after rolling and cutting, leave pasta to dry for <b>1-2 hours<b> on a floured cloth","To increase quantity, add <b>1 extra<b> egg per added <b>100 g flour.<b> The maximum quantity at any one time is <b>500 g flour<b> and <b>5 eggs.<b> Increase kneading time to <b>3 minutes.<b>","<strong>Green<\/strong> <strong>pasta dough<\/strong>: use basic recipe with added <b>100 g flour<b> and <b>70 g spinach<b> leaves (fresh, clean and dry; or frozen, defrosted and water squeezed out). Place <b>300 g flour<b> and spinach leaves into mixing bowl and mix <b><strong>20 sec\/speed 9.<\/strong><b> Add eggs and oil and knead <b><strong>2 min\/.<\/strong><b>","<strong>Red pasta dough without eggs<\/strong>: instead of <b>2 eggs,<b> use <b>100 g tomato<b> juice and proceed as directed by the recipe."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","1h","4 portions"]}